      "died_year": 1918,
      "bio": "Richard Fitzhugh (1834\u20131918) was a pharmacist and prominent public figure in Nottingham. He was a partner in Fitzhugh & Carr, chemists of 21 Greyhound Street, Nottingham. He served as a Justice of the Peace and was Lord Mayor of Nottingham in 1891\u201392. He lived at 3 Clumber Crescent South with his wife Maria Louisa and their children.",
