      "died_date": "15 June 1900",
      "died_year": 1900,
      "bio": "Richard Truman Fitzhugh (b. 1872; d. 15 June 1900). Educated at Nottingham Grammar School and Shrewsbury Grammar School. He trained as a doctor at Guy's Hospital and was awarded a Bachelor of Medicine, University of London, in 1898. He served as a doctor during the Boer War and died of enteric fever (typhoid) at the Imperial Yeomanry Base Hospital at Deelfontein, South Africa, aged 28.",
